Detailed Description

A basic object.

Each object holds a pointer to the trackers that track it. This pointer is useful so that the trackers can be notified if the object is released.

Each up-class of this basic object class hold an object type that acts just like RTTI to provide a safe way to up-cast.

Member Function Documentation

void FUObject::Detach (   )  [protected]
 

Detaches all the trackers of this object.

The trackers will be notified that this object has been released. It is not recommended to call this function outside of a destructor.
